# Phishing Email Investigation

## Alert Overview
A suspicious email was flagged by the monitoring system due to characteristics commonly associated with phishing attempts.
The message appeared to impersonate a known external supplier and requested urgent action from the recipient.

## Detection Source
Email security monitoring / SIEM correlation

## Observed Indicators
- Sender domain visually similar to legitimate supplier
- Urgent payment-related language
- Embedded external hyperlink
- Unexpected request context

## Analyst Assessment
The email shows clear indicators of a credential-harvesting phishing attempt.  
The link redirects to a non-corporate domain designed to capture user login details.  
No evidence was found that the user interacted with the link at the time of review.

## Potential Risk
If the link had been accessed and credentials entered, unauthorized system access and potential data exposure could occur.

## Actions Taken
- Email removed from user mailbox
- Sender domain blocked
- User notified of phishing attempt
- Environment checked for similar emails

## Escalation Considerations
Escalation required if:
- User confirms link interaction
- Credentials were entered
- Additional recipients identified

## Notes
No confirmed compromise identified during analysis.
